stylometry: @RISK shows you the histogram of your distribution, the standard deviation, mean, maximum, minimum, and other statistical values you might want to take a look at depending on how in depth you would like to go with a simulation or problem. You are looking at the mean profit, the maximum and minimum profit, the standard deviation of profit. You want to order the demand that will not only give you a high profit, but will have a lower standard deviation so you are sure that your profit will not vary much from the mean. You also will ideally want a higher minimum and maximum profit. This does not necessarily mean you order the number of calendars that gives you the highest mean profit. If the highest mean profit has one of the lower standard deviations, my company would make the decision of slightly losing profit for a higher standard deviation to have less variation of the possible profit.
